1. Source Code.
The term "source code" means the preferred form of the work for making modifications to it.  It is exhibited in a form that may be used to create and install the work.  A "work based on the Program" means either the Program or any derivative work under copyright law: that is to say, you can modify the Program, and you can also incorporate parts of it into other programs.

